<para>One use case for <link linkend="_namespace_luthetus_1_1_common_1_1_razor_lib_1_1_installations_1_1_models_1a761f9bfb52cfd9ffaa1a4bbdddf1aebb">LuthetusHostingInformation</link> would be service registration.<?linebreak?><?linebreak?> If one uses <link linkend="_namespace_luthetus_1_1_common_1_1_razor_lib_1_1_installations_1_1_models_1a6fa014b5a7072b6304fd9fe595cc2a60a8fb53cb4338611e251a9bb003961f984">LuthetusHostingKind.ServerSide</link>, then services.AddHostedService&lt;TService&gt;(...); will be invoked.<?linebreak?><?linebreak?> Whereas, if one uses <link linkend="_namespace_luthetus_1_1_common_1_1_razor_lib_1_1_installations_1_1_models_1a6fa014b5a7072b6304fd9fe595cc2a60af93da81fd23e2eeaf8de29b04bb2399f">LuthetusHostingKind.Wasm</link> then services.AddSingleton&lt;TService&gt;(...); will be used. Then after the initial render, a Task will be &apos;fire and forget&apos; invoked to start the service. </para>
